d in the figures.</p><p>4. Only includes pupils who are resident in England.</p><p>5. “All other pupils” includes pupils not eligible for free school meals and for whom free school meal eligibility was unclassified or could not be determined.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","28752","2016-03-07T17:44:54.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455717/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455717/answer","28751 and 28752 data attachment.xlsx","28751 and 28752 data attachment.xlsx","Data ","Data ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455717/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-02-26","Children: Communication Skills","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many reception year children in Ashfield constituency reached the expected levels in speech and communication skills in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","28751"
