"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455168","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-07","<p>Ministers and officials are in regular contact with the Tunisian authorities, including on the matter of Travel Advice. The most recent discussions were in February 2016 when the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my hon. Friend the Member for Bournemouth East (Mr Ellwood), met the Tunisian Ambassador in London, and the Chargé d’ Affairs in Tunis met the Ministers for Foreign Affairs, Tourism and Interior.</p><p>We keep our travel advice for Tunisia under constant review, taking into account the current terrorist threat and the Tunisian capacity to deter and respond to that threat. The safety of British nationals abroad remains our priority.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-03-07T15:48:23.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455168/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455168/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455168/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-25","Tunisia: Travel Information","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what meetings they have had recently with the government of Tunisia to discuss the current travel advice for UK citizens intending to travel to Tunisia; and whether they have any plans to amend that advice.","false","Biography information for Baroness Suttie",,"Baroness Suttie","HL6473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455169","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-07","Following the terrorist attacks in Sousse the British Government made a commitment to help the Tunisian government improve its security arrangements. This includes helping them improve their counter-terrorism capacity and ability to protect tourists, including British nationals. The UK continues to lead on providing expertise and mentoring for protective security with support from international partners. We do not release details of specific counter-terrorism activities for operational and security reasons.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-03-07T15:48:47.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455169/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455169/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455169/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-25","Tunisia: Tourism","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they are funding training for the Tunisian tourism industry in order to improve their security arrangements, and if so, by how much.","false","Biography information for Baroness Suttie",,"Baroness Suttie","HL6474"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455170","Department for International Development","false","2016-03-08","<p>Since 2014, UNHCR has co-ordinated inter-agency efforts to prepare for a possible influx of refugees and asylum-seekers from Libya, at the request of the Tunisian government and in close cooperation with UN agencies and partners. Its most recent assessment reported that there were 928 people of concern residing in Tunisia, mostly from Syria.</p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2016-03-08T17:19:15.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455170/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455170/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455170/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-02-25","Libya: Refugees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the number of Libyan refugees currently residing in Tunisia.","false","Biography information for Baroness Suttie",,"Baroness Suttie","HL6475"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455171","Department for International Development","false","2016-03-08","<p>Final decisions on who will be in the delegation will be taken nearer the time.</p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2016-03-08T17:14:13.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455171/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455171/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455171/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-02-25","World Humanitarian Summit","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government who will represent them at the forthcoming World Humanitarian Summit in May.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL6476"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455172","Department for International Development","false","2016-03-08","<p>The UK has four objectives for the Summit. Most importantly we want to see a renewed commitment to the protection of civilians in conflict, but also more effective financing, a new approach to building resilience to natural hazards before they take place, and a stronger focus on protecting and empowering women and girls. The global community – humanitarian, development and political actors – must come together to address these challenges.</p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2016-03-08T17:17:58.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455172/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455172/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455172/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-02-25","World Humanitarian Summit","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what their priorities are at the forthcoming World Humanitarian Summit in May.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL6477"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455173","Department for International Development","false","2016-03-08","<p>The UK is committed to making the World Humanitarian Summit a success and recognises that this requires coordination with a large number of interested parties.</p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2016-03-08T17:20:29.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455173/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455173/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455173/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-02-25","World Humanitarian Summit","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to work with the UK members of parliament who are attending the forthcoming World Humanitarian Summit in May.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL6478"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455174","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-08","<p>This Government has demonstrated its commitment to the war powers convention by its willingness to hold Parliamentary debates in relation to air strikes in Iraq and Syria in 2013, 2014 and 2015. However, we have no intention of defining the precise circumstances, including the identity of specific military units, capabilities or types of operation, under which we might be obliged to act first and to notify Parliament afterwards, in order to avoid presenting our adversaries with opportunities to exploit that definition against the UK or our interests.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-03-08T17:04:59.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455174/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455174/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455174/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Libya: Military Intervention","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Earl Howe on 22 February (HL5864), whether the term UK troops includes members of 13 Squadron, based at RAF Waddington, and of 39 Squadron, based at Creech Air Force Base in the US.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL6479"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455175","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-08","<p>The build time of a submarine is measured between the start of manufacture and operational handover to the Royal Navy. Using this metric, the build time of HMS Astute was 170 months and for Artful was 137 months.</p><p>Keel laying and commissioning have no bearing on the build programme. These are ceremonial milestones only: commissioning can happen before or after operational handover. Using these milestones, however, the time taken from keel laying to commissioning was nine years and seven months for HMS Astute and 11 years for Artful.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-03-08T17:00:32.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455175/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455175/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455175/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Astute Class Submarines","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Earl Howe on 19 January (HL4885), whether the dates given in fact show that the time from laying down to operational handover for HMS Astute was nine years and seven months, and that for HMS Artful it will be 11 years.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL6480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455176","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-17","<p>The Cabinet Office's interim guidance on applying the new clause in government grant agreements can be found online at:<br>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/interim-guidance-on-applying-a-new-clause-in-government-grant-agreements<br> <br>Grant agreements are routinely subject to conditions, as well as a monitoring/audit process. The new grant clause builds on those existing processes</p><p><br>The new clause has successfully been trialled by the Department for Communities and Local Government over the last 12 months.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2016-03-17T17:45:24.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455176/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455176/answer","HL6481 Implementation_Guidance_for_Departments_on_Anti-Lobbying_Clause.pdf","HL6481 Implementation_Guidance_for_Departments_on_Anti-Lobbying_Clause.pdf","Attachment","Attachment","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455176/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-25","Charities: Lobbying","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Bridges of Headley on 25 February (HL6124), what is their definition of "political campaigning and lobbying", and how they expect charities to establish that any expenditure on such campaigning and lobbying is funded exclusively from their own resources.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL6481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455184","Attorney General","false","2016-03-01","<p>The Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) does all that it can to make sure that administrative errors do not prevent victims from giving evidence at trial.</p><p> </p><p>The CPS introduced a national standard operating practice for magistrates’ court activity in May 2015. The process is digital and task-based and is designed to ensure consistency of approach and timing of activity in managing casework which will further reduce the risk of administrative errors being made. Testing of Crown Court standard operating practice commenced at the beginning of February 2016.</p><p> </p><p>Joint police/CPS Witness Care Units (WCUs) provide a single point of contact for victims and witnesses and ensure they have access to tailored support to make sure they are able to attend court and give their best evidence. Most WCUs use the Witness Management System (WMS) to record the contact they have with victims and witnesses. WMS is a bespoke IT system designed to support WCUs in managing their cases, thereby reducing the risk of administrative errors.</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2016-03-01T14:39:39.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455184/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455184/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455184/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2016-02-25","Trials","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what steps the CPS has taken to ensure that administrative errors do not prevent victims from giving evidence at trial.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","28443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455185","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-08","<p>I replied to the hon. Member on 4 March.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-03-08T14:41:01.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455185/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455185/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455185/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-25","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, when he plans to reply to the letter of 18 January 2016 from the hon. Member for North East Fife on the Royal Mail's dismissal of David Mitchell.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","28442"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455186","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-01","<p>Section 45 of the Employment Rights Act 1996 gives certain shop workers and betting workers the right not to be subjected to detriment by their employers on the ground that the employee refused (or proposed to refuse) to do shop work, or betting work, on Sundays. This right can be enforced by bringing a complaint to the employment tribunal. There is no relevant criminal offence, so there have been no prosecutions.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-03-01T15:28:29.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455186/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455186/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455186/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-25","Sunday Trading: Prosecutions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many successful prosecutions there have been against employers who have taken action against workers who have refused to work on Sundays under Section 45 of the Employment Rights Act 1996.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","28491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455187","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-04","<p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills is continuing to monitor the impact of <em>Lock v British Gas</em> and other court decisions relating to holiday pay. We are undertaking a formal assessment of the financial impact and will make that available as and when there is a quality assured estimate.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-03-04T13:33:14.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455187/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455187/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455187/answer","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455187/answer/previousversion/48360","Biography information for Nick Boles","26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-25","Holiday Leave: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the financial effect on businesses of the decision in Loch v British Gas has on, including payments of bonus and commission in the calculation of holiday pay.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","28521"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455188","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-03","<p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills keeps the working time regulations under continuous review. We will continue to engage with interested parties to determine the best way forward in this area.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-03-03T17:25:28.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455188/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455188/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455188/answer","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455188/answer/previousversion/48362","Biography information for Nick Boles","26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-25","Working Hours: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what plans he has to bring forward legislative proposals to amend the working time regulations; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","28523"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455189","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-01","<p>The European Commission has published a large number of documents relating to the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership (TTIP) on its website, including EU proposals for legal text, position papers and factsheets.</p><p> </p><p>The Commission and the US have agreed that national parliamentarians should have access to classified TTIP documents, including consolidated texts, via reading rooms in national ministries. Restrictions placed on these rooms include that they are only accessible to officials of Member State central governments and Members of Member State national Parliaments.</p><p> </p><p>The UK intends to establish such a reading room in the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS). This will give equivalent access to documents for Members of both Houses to that afforded to Members of the European Parliament. Members of both Houses will be informed of the process and details of how to access the room shortly, once these have been finalised.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-03-01T17:55:18.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455189/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455189/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455189/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-25","Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will place in the Library the most recent submissions made by the parties involved in the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership negotiations.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","28524"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455190","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-01","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>In 2006 Indepen were commissioned by the DTI to evaluate the economic costs and benefits of extending Sunday Trading hours, a copy of the report can be found on the GOV.UK website.</p><p> </p><p>My Department has not commissioned any research since then into the effects of the extension of Sunday opening hours.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-03-01T15:26:19.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455190/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455190/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455190/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-25","Sunday Trading: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what research has been commissioned by his Department into the effects of the extension of Sunday opening hours in each year for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","28540"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455191","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-03","<p>The Government’s Family Test is not a pass or fail measure.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has conscientiously considered the impact on families and the evidence on this presented during the consultation. The Government will publish the Impact Assessment, including the Family Test, shortly.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-03-03T17:16:00.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455191/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455191/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455191/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-25","Sunday Trading: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether his proposals for the extension of Sunday trading hours has passed the family test.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","28528"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455192","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-09","<p>My right hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Business Innovation and Skills, BIS Ministers and officials are in frequent contact with a wide range of stakeholders on labour market issues, including issues around internships. The Low Pay Commission also consults on a range of issues, including internships, and submits its findings to Government each year to inform its recommendations on the National Minimum Wage. We are not aware of any recent, formal representations relating only to exploitation of unpaid interns in the specified sectors.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-03-09T11:52:09.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455192/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455192/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455192/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-25","Work Experience","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many representations he has received on the exploitation of unpaid trials in the (a) service, (b) print and (c) retail sector.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","28558"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455193","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-11","<p>Entitlement to the National Minimum Wage (NMW) applies where someone meets the criteria of a worker. There is no legal or consistently-used definition of an internship and therefore no authoritative, single assessment of their prevalence, unpaid or otherwise. However, the Low Pay Commission 2015 Report on the National Minimum Wage sets out their findings from the evidence they have collated as well as research that they have commissioned to assess the prevalence of unpaid internships.</p><p>The Government works to promote high-quality, paid internships through improved codes of practice, awareness campaigns and changes to the BIS-sponsored Graduate Talent Pool. We also continue to tackle exploitation. The Government invested over £13m in 2015/16 to ensure enforcement of the NMW and we continue to name and shame employers who break minimum wage law.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-03-11T17:00:06.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455193/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455193/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455193/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-25","Work Experience","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the prevalence of the exploitation of unpaid trials in at-risk sectors.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","28559"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455194","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-10","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given on 2 March 2016 by my hon. Friend the Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for Justice to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2016-02-25/28629/" target="_blank">28629</a>.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-03-10T15:39:56.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455194/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455194/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455194/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-25","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Employment Tribunals Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how much his Department spent from the public purse on industrial tribunals in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28617"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455195","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-10","<p>During the period of the last six years there have been no early terminations of consultants’ contracts for the Department of Business, Innovation and Skills.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-03-10T15:44:11.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455195/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455195/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455195/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-25","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many consultants' contracts were terminated early in each of the last six years for which figures are available; and what the cost of each such termination was in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28649"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455196","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-14","<p>My Department does not hold a central list of publications, consultations or circulars.</p><p>All publications, consultations, press releases and statistics are published on the GOV.UK website and can be found listed there:</p><p>Publications: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=department-for-business-innovation-skills" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=department-for-business-innovation-skills</a></p><p>Consultations: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=department-for-business-innovation-skills&amp;publication_filter_option=consultations" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=department-for-business-innovation-skills&amp;publication_filter_option=consultations</a></p><p>Press releases: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/announcements?departments%5B%5D=department-for-business-innovation-skills" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/announcements?departments%5B%5D=department-for-business-innovation-skills</a></p><p>Statistics: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics?departments%5B%5D=department-for-business-innovation-skills" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics?departments%5B%5D=department-for-business-innovation-skills</a></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-03-14T15:18:27.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455196/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455196/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455196/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-25","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Publications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many (a) publications, (b) consultation documents and (c) circulars his Department has issued since August 2012; and what the title was of each such publication, consultation document or circular.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28665"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455197","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-10","<p>The information requested is not available because separate data for cases based wholly or partially on the Human Rights Act 1998 are not recorded.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-03-10T15:42:13.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455197/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455197/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455197/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-25","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Human Rights Act 1998","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many civil law suits have been brought against his Department based either wholly or partially on grounds provided by the Human Rights Act 1998; how many such suits were settled out of court before a court judgment was delivered; and how much such settlements have cost the public purse since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28633"
