"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455244","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-02","<p>The answer can be found by using the publicly available filters on GOV.UK:</p><p>The Department has published 2,111 publications. Details, with full titles of each publication, can be viewed at:</p><p>a) <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=&amp;publication_filter_option=all&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=department-for-communities-and-local-government&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=01%2F08%2F2012&amp;to_date" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=&amp;publication_filter_option=all&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=department-for-communities-and-local-government&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=01%2F08%2F2012&amp;to_date</a>=</p><p>The Department has published 189 consultations. Details can be viewed at:</p><p>b) <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=&amp;publication_filter_option=consultations&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=department-for-communities-and-local-government&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=01%2F08%2F2012&amp;to_date" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=&amp;publication_filter_option=consultations&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=department-for-communities-and-local-government&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=01%2F08%2F2012&amp;to_date</a>=</p><p>The Department has published 44 circulars. Details can be viewed at:</p><p>c) <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=circulars&amp;publication_filter_option=all&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=department-for-communities-and-local-government&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=01%2F08%2F2012&amp;to_date" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=circulars&amp;publication_filter_option=all&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=department-for-communities-and-local-government&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=01%2F08%2F2012&amp;to_date</a>=</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-03-02T17:28:15.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455244/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455244/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455244/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-25","Department for Communities and Local Government: Publications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many (a) publications, (b) consultation documents and (c) circulars his Department has issued since August 2012; and what the title was of each such publication, consultation document or circular.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455245","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-03","<p>The local government finance settlement distributed revenue support grant by looking at the main resources that are available to local councils. The Local Government Finance Report (England) 2016/2017 sets out the basis of this distribution and the results can be found at;</p><p><br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/final-local-government-finance-settlement-england-2016-to-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/final-local-government-finance-settlement-england-2016-to-2017</a>.</p><p>.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-03-03T10:57:54.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455245/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455245/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455245/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-25","Local Government Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what criteria his Department uses to determine the level of supplementary funding provided to local authorities as part of the local government finance settlement.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","28552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455246","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-04","<p>The cost of Employment Tribunals can be found within the HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service annual accounts published at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/433948/hmcts-annual-report-accounts-2014-15.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/433948/hmcts-annual-report-accounts-2014-15.pdf</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-03-04T14:06:29.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455246/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455246/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455246/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-25","Department for Communities and Local Government: Employment Tribunals Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much his Department spent from the public purse on industrial tribunals in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455247","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-07","<p>My rt. hon. Friend, the Secretary of State (Greg Clark) meets with my rt. hon. Friend, the Home Secretary (Theresa May) on a regular basis to discuss a range of government matters.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-03-07T15:19:38.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455247/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455247/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455247/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-25","Mayors: Tower Hamlets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what discussions he has had with the Home Secretary on the decisions of the Electoral Court's ruling on the 2014 mayoral election in Tower Hamlets.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","28557"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455248","Department of Health","false","2016-03-04","<p>The Department of Health has responsibility for adult social care policy which includes the activities of social workers in adult settings. The Department for Education has responsibility for the activities of social workers in children’s services.</p><p> </p><p>The Health and Social Care Information Centre has recently published its report “Personal Social Services: Staff of Social Services Departments, England, as at September 2015”. This shows that the vacancy rates for adult social workers in local authorities are as follows:</p><p> </p><p>2014 there were 1,100* vacancies (8%)</p><p>2015 there were 1,700** vacancies (12%)</p><p> </p><p>*2014 based on 121 councils with vacancies data recorded.</p><p>**2015 based on 133 councils with vacancies data recorded.</p><p> </p><p>Source: Skills for Care - NMDS-SC</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-03-04T14:01:39.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455248/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455248/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455248/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-25","Social Workers: Vacancies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many social worker vacancies remained unfilled in (a) 2014 and (b) 2015.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","28543"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455249","Department for Transport","false","2016-03-04","<p>The Road Safety Statement published on 21 December 2015 outlines what the Department is currently doing to improve road safety. For example, we are currently consulting on increasing the penalty points and financial penalty for those who commit the offence of using a mobile phone whilst driving.</p><p> </p><p>We have previously introduced fixed penalty notices in order to assist the police in dealing more effectively with careless driving. This would enable more people to be offered rehabilitative education to combat such behaviour.</p><p> </p><p>Britain is a world leader in road safety, but we are always striving to improve. For example, from 2 March 2015 it has been an offence to drive with certain drugs in your body in excess of official limits. I have provided £1million to further increase enforcement during the THINK! campaign that commenced on 29 February and will run through March thus coinciding with the 1<sup>st</sup> anniversary of the commencement of the new offence.</p><p> </p><p>Sentencing and enforcement policy issues are matters for the Ministry of Justice and Home Office respectively.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-03-04T11:16:52.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455249/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455249/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455249/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-25","Dangerous Driving","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps the Government is taking to reduce the prevalence of reckless driving.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","28508"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455250","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-03","<p>The Ministerial Working Group on Homelessness re-convened on 13 January, bringing together key Departments to coordinate policy across Government to prevent more households becoming homeless. The group will meet again shortly to agree its priorities and future work programme.</p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-03-03T10:57:12.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455250/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455250/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455250/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-25","Ministerial Working Group on Preventing and Tackling Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what work the Ministerial Working Group for Homelessness has conducted since its last meeting.","false","Biography information for David Mackintosh","Northampton South","David Mackintosh","28519"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455251","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-07","<p>My rt. hon. Friend, the Secretary of State (Greg Clark) has received no formal assessment from the Tower Hamlets Commissioners regarding the level of fraud in the borough. The Secretary of State is aware that the Commissioners have contributed both written and oral evidence to my rt. hon. Friend, the Member for Brentwood and Ongar (Sir Eric Pickles’) review on electoral fraud.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-03-07T15:16:08.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455251/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455251/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455251/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-25","Fraud: Tower Hamlets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment has been made by the Commissioners appointed by his Department to the London Borough of Tower Hamlets of the level of fraud in that borough.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","28598"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455252","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-04","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-03-04T14:03:22.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455252/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455252/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455252/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-25","Department for Communities and Local Government: Human Rights Act 1998","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many civil law suits have been brought against his Department based either wholly or partially on grounds provided by the Human Rights Act 1998; how many such suits were settled out of court before a court judgment was delivered; and how much such settlements have cost the public purse since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28635"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455253","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-04","<p>The Department already publishes spend on overtime on a monthly basis as part of wider transparency publications. The Department's workforce management publications can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/workforce-management" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/workforce-management</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-03-04T14:04:00.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455253/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455253/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455253/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-25","Department for Communities and Local Government: Overtime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much his Department has paid to staff in overtime in each of the last 24 months.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28683"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455254","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-04","<p>Sums paid to Department for Culture, Media and Sport (DCMS) staff for overtime for the last 24 months, for which figures are available, were as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>£000s</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>January</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>February</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>March</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>April</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>May</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>June</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>July</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>August</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>September</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>October</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>November</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>December</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>5.1</p></td><td><p>10.9</p></td><td><p>2.6</p></td><td><p>6.8</p></td><td><p>4.3</p></td><td><p>7.3</p></td><td><p>23.7</p></td><td><p>7.0</p></td><td><p>7.1</p></td><td><p>3.7</p></td><td><p>10.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>2.2</p></td><td><p>3.9</p></td><td><p>28.0</p></td><td><p>6.2</p></td><td><p>31.0</p></td><td><p>5.8</p></td><td><p>4.3</p></td><td><p>8.3</p></td><td><p>6.6</p></td><td><p>4.3</p></td><td><p>8.6</p></td><td><p>7.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>6.3</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>DCMS is the smallest government department, with 509 full time equivalent (FTE) permanent employees (as of 31 January 2016). Overtime is a cost-effective way of managing peaks in workload in order to reduce the need for contractors or adding to the department's headcount. Annual expenditure on overtime accounts for just under 0.3% of the DCMS paybill.</p><p><br>DCMS has responsibility for high profile policy, which includes staging national First World War commemoration events - this is reflected in our overtime figures for August 2014 and May 2015.</p><p><br>Recent machinery of government changes has also seen DCMS take on additional policy areas, including the digital economy unit, digital inclusion, data protection, the sponsorship of the National Archives and the Information Commissioner. The figure for March 2015 reflects the addition of the 2014-15 total overtime cost for the Digital Economy Unit following its Machinery of Government transfer to DCMS; monthly analysis of this sum is not available.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-03-04T13:37:27.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455254/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455254/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455254/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-25","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Overtime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much his Department has paid to staff in overtime in each of the last 24 months.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28684"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455255","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-04","<p>We do not have any information on civil law suits have been brought against the Department based either wholly or partially on grounds provided by the Human Rights Act 1998.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-03-04T10:55:49.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455255/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455255/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455255/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-25","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Human Rights Act 1998","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many civil law suits have been brought against his Department based either wholly or partially on grounds provided by the Human Rights Act 1998; how many such suits were settled out of court before a court judgment was delivered; and how much such settlements have cost the public purse since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28636"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455256","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-02","<p>The cost of Employment Tribunals can be found within the HMCTS annual accounts published at<em>: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/433948/hmcts-annual-report-accounts-2014-15.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/433948/hmcts-annual-report-accounts-2014-15.pd</a></em></p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-03-02T15:43:58.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455256/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455256/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455256/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-25","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Employment Tribunals Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much his Department spent from the public purse on industrial tribunals in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455257","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-04","<p>DCMS shares premises with other Government Departments - HMRC and DfE - that are responsible for the employment and payment of cleaning staff.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-03-04T13:30:06.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455257/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455257/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455257/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-25","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Cleaning Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the rate of pay is for cleaners in his Department.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","28600"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455258","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-04","<p>The answer can be found by using the publicly available filters on <a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">GOV.UK</a>:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department has published 692 publications. Details, with full titles of each publication, can be viewed at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=&amp;publication_filter_option=all&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=department-for-culture-media-sport&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=01%2F08%2F2012&amp;to_date=" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=&amp;publication_filter_option=all&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=department-for-culture-media-sport&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=01%2F08%2F2012&amp;to_date=</a></p><p>The Department has published 60 consultations. Details can be viewed at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=&amp;publication_filter_option=consultations&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=department-for-culture-media-sport&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=01%2F08%2F2012&amp;to_date=" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=&amp;publication_filter_option=consultations&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=department-for-culture-media-sport&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=01%2F08%2F2012&amp;to_date=</a></p><p>The Department has published no Circulars in the timeframe.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=circulars&amp;publication_filter_option=all&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=department-for-culture-media-sport&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=01%2F08%2F2012&amp;to_date=" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=circulars&amp;publication_filter_option=all&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=department-for-culture-media-sport&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=01%2F08%2F2012&amp;to_date=</a></p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-03-04T13:46:03.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455258/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455258/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455258/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-25","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Publications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many (a) publications, (b) consultation documents and (c) circulars his Department has issued since August 2012; and what the title was of each such publication, consultation document or circular.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28668"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455259","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-03","<p>DCMS has not terminated early any fixed fee consultancy contracts, where a cost might have been incurred, in the said time frame.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-03-03T14:01:58.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455259/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455259/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455259/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-25","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many consultants' contracts were terminated early in each of the last six years for which figures are available; and what the cost of each such termination was in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28652"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455260","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-02","<p>Details of my and the Minister for Sport and Tourism’s meetings with representatives of the bookmaking industry are available via the Department's transparency returns, which can be found at: https://www.gov.uk/search?q=quarterly+ministerial+returns&amp;filter_organisations%5B%5D=department-for-culture-media-sport</p><p> </p><p>In addition, my officials have met representatives of bookmakers on numerous occasions to discuss issues related to gambling.</p><p> </p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-03-02T17:36:39.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455260/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455260/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455260/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-25","Gambling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, on how many occasions he or officials of his Department have met representatives of high street bookmakers to discuss gambling since May 2015.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","28475"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455261","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-01","<p>The Department uprates War Pensions annually in line with the Consumer Prices Index (CPI), ensuring a consistent approach to social security disability benefits administered by the Department for Work and Pensions. This is in keeping with other public service schemes and reflects the measure of inflation used by the Bank of England. Therefore the Ministry of Defence has no plans to estimate the cost of uprating compensation payments made under the War Pension Scheme in line with average earnings.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-03-01T16:57:58.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455261/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455261/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455261/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","War Pensions: Uprating","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Written Statement by the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Defence of 9 December 2015, HCWS372, on War Pension Scheme - Uprating 2016, if he will make an estimate of the cost of uprating war pensions in line with average earnings in 2016.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","28481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455262","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-01","<p>The two new Queen Elizabeth Class (QEC) aircraft carriers, currently under construction in Rosyth have a planned service life of 50 years each. They will be capable of a spectrum of roles including battlefield helicopter support to littoral operations. The Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 made provision to enhance this capability in the QEC aircraft carriers.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","28006","2016-03-01T16:32:12.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455262/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455262/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455262/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Aircraft Carriers: Littoral Warfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to paragraph 4.47 of the National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, which of the two Queen Elizabeth class aircraft carriers will be enhanced to support amphibious capability.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","28464"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455263","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-01","<p>Much of the work to decommission Royal Navy ships is undertaken using contracts that provide support services for all ships conducting Fleet activities at HM Naval Base, Portsmouth. Costs are not attributed to individual vessels.</p><p>Defence Equipment &amp; Support (DE&amp;S) will be responsible for the removal of classified equipment and known hazardous materials from HMS OCEAN after the ship has been decommissioned. The DE&amp;S financial plan will include a provision for this work but a figure has yet to be approved.</p><p>The Disposal Services Authority (DSA), part of DE&amp;S, disposes of defence equipment that is surplus to requirement. DSA costs are not attributed to individual platforms and information is not held in the format requested.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","28002","2016-03-01T17:36:57.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455263/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455263/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455263/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","HMS Ocean: Decommissioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 1 February 2016 to Question 24278, how much has been set aside within his Department's budget to cover potential costs associated with the decommissioning and disposal of HMS Ocean.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","28465"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455264","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-01","<p>Following our initial evidence to the Armed Forces Pay Review Body (AFPRB) in 2014 we undertook to conduct a more fundamental review of commitment bonuses during 2015, once New Employment Model proposals had matured. Our intention was to submit further evidence to the AFPRB. However, as announced on 23 November 2015, and detailed in the Government's National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, a decision was taken as part of this wider review to phase out commitment bonuses. This decision reflected the view that there was insufficient evidence to prove a tangible retention benefit from these payments. All such payments will now cease from 1 April 2021, providing affected personnel time to adjust their financial plans to take account of any payments for which they are no longer eligible.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-03-01T16:57:01.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455264/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455264/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455264/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Armed Forces: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to paragraph 3.58 of the 44th Report of the Armed Forces Pay Review Body, published in March 2015, when the review of military commitment bonuses was completed; and if he will publish that review.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","28471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455265","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-01","<p>We assess that the Afghan Taliban leadership opposes Daesh's presence in Afghanistan, where there has been reported fighting between the two groups. Our judgement is that the Taliban generate funding via illegal exploitation of Afghanistan's natural resources, for example marble, talcum and lapis lazuli, and through extortion of payments from legal mining operations, but we have seen no evidence to suggest that Daesh is currently engaged in these activities.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-03-01T16:32:53.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455265/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455265/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455265/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Afghanistan: Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment his Department has made of the existence of links between the Taliban and Islamic State movements in Afghanistan and the abusive exploitation of extractive resources.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","28434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455266","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-29","<p>This information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-02-29T17:14:26.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455266/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455266/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455266/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Ministry of Defence: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many consultants' contracts were terminated early in each of the last six years for which figures are available; and what the cost of each such termination was in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28653"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455267","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-01","<p>The requested information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-03-01T16:55:57.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455267/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455267/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455267/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Ministry of Defence: Publications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) publications, (b) consultation documents and (c) circulars his Department has issued since August 2012; and what the title was of each such publication, consultation document or circular.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455268","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-02","<p>The production of manufacturing drawings is phased to support corresponding manufacturing activities and has commenced for long-lead elements of the Successor submarine including the propulsion plant and missile tubes.</p><p>Production of the majority of manufacturing drawings will not commence until after the next approval.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-03-02T16:15:28.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455268/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455268/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455268/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Trident Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of the elements of the Successor programme has commenced production of manufacturing drawings; and when he expects all elements of that to have commenced such drawing.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","28560"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455269","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-01","<p>Cleaning within the Ministry of Defence is undertaken through estate maintenance contracts and therefore information on the rates of pay for cleaners is held by a number of third parties and not by the Department.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-03-01T16:55:12.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455269/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455269/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455269/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Ministry of Defence: Cleaning Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the rate of pay is for cleaners in his Department.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","28601"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455270","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-03","<p>The cost of Employment Tribunals can be found within the HM Courts and Tribunals Service annual accounts published at<em>: </em></p><p><em>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/433948/hmcts-annual-report-accounts-2014-15.pdf.</em></p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-03-03T16:10:02.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455270/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455270/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455270/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Ministry of Defence: Employment Tribunals Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department spent from the public purse on industrial tribunals in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455271","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-01","<p>As set out in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, we will further invest around £600 million in the design of the Successor submarine as we prepare to move to the demonstration phase. Options for the subsequent investment stages and their scope, time and cost are currently under consideration and will be subject to the formal approvals process</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-03-01T16:59:11.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455271/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455271/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455271/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Trident Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the next three stages are in the investment programme announced in the Strategic Defence and Security Review for the Successor programme; and when he expects each of those stages will reach approval decisions.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","28561"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455272","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-01","<p>Membership of the Defence Nuclear Executive Board consists of the:</p><p>Permanent Secretary</p><p>Vice Chief of the Defence Staff</p><p>Director General Finance</p><p>Director General Security Policy</p><p>Deputy Chief of Defence Staff Military Capability</p><p>Chief Scientific Advisor</p><p>Fleet Commander</p><p>The Terms of Reference for the Board are currently being reviewed. The Board sits quarterly and has met four times since January 2015; it reports to Ministers via the Defence Board.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-03-01T16:59:56.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455272/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455272/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455272/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Nuclear Enterprise Board","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, who the members of the nuclear enterprise board are; what the terms of reference are of that board; how many times that board has met since January 2015; and how that board reports to ministers.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","28514"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455273","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-03","<p>I am withholding information on the operational activity of Royal Navy ships and on what operational reports Ministers receive as their disclosure would or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-03-03T16:01:52.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455273/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455273/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455273/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Iran: Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 16 February 2016 to Question 26667, whether HMS Defender tracked the Iranian UAV that was reported to have flown in close proximity to the USS Harry S Truman; and what reports he has received on other instances of Iranian UAV activity in the Persian Gulf.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","28485"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455274","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-02","<p>The recommendations include fourteen that are are technical in nature and two that are administrative. We are currently reviewing the Independent Power and Propulsion System Performance Review, to determine what redactions are necessary before a copy is placed in the Library of the House. As part of this process, we are considering what information about the sixteen recommendations can be released.</p><p> </p><p>On the question of the adoption of those recommendations, I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave her to question 28036 on 1 March 2015.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-03-02T16:14:57.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455274/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455274/answer","20150103_28036_Type_45_Destroyers.docx","20150103_28036_Type_45_Destroyers.docx","QnA extract on Type 45 Destroyers","QnA extract on Type 45 Destroyers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455274/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Type 45 Destroyers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 9 February 2016 to Question 25153, what the 16 recommendations are of the Independent Power and Propulsion System Performance Review are; on which Type 45 Destroyers all those recommendations have been implemented in full; and when he expects the implementation of all those recommendations to be completed across the class.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","28497"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455275","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-01","<p>I refer the hon.Member to the answer I gave her on 29 February 2016 to Question 28003.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-03-01T16:41:11.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455275/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455275/answer","2060229_28003_Type_45_Destroyers.docx","2060229_28003_Type_45_Destroyers.docx","QnA extract on NATO Type 45 Destroyers","QnA extract on NATO Type 45 Destroyers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455275/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","NATO: Type 45 Destroyers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to his Department's press release, UK to step up NATO maritime commitment, of 10 February 2016, which Type 45 Destroyers he expects will be deployed to NATO's Standing Maritime Group 1 in October 2016.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","28498"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455276","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-03","<p>The information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-03-03T16:03:08.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455276/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455276/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455276/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Ministry of Defence: Human Rights Act 1998","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many civil law suits have been brought against his Department based either wholly or partially on grounds provided by the Human Rights Act 1998; how many such suits were settled out of court before a court judgment was delivered; and how much such settlements have cost the public purse since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28637"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455277","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-03","<p>The Royal Navy routinely allocates vessels to NATO's Standing Maritime Groups and Standing Countermeasures Groups, which are multinational, integrated maritime forces permanently available to NATO to perform tasks ranging from participating in exercises to intervention missions.</p><p>This year the UK's contribution consists of: three Mine Countermeasures Vessels, on four month deployments in rotation; one Frigate for six months, which is the first to be deployed to this task since 2010; and a Destroyer, from October 2016.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-03-03T16:04:32.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455277/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455277/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455277/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Navy: Baltic Sea","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the role is of the five additional UK Royal Naval vessels situated in the Baltic.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","28576"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455278","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-04","<p>The UK undertakes a wide range of operational, Defence Engagement and training activity within the Baltic region. While it is not possible to provide full information, costs exceeded £1.6 million in FY13-14; £13.5 million in FY14-15 and £4.1 million in FY15-16.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-03-04T14:36:16.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455278/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455278/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455278/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Armed Forces: Baltic States","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the cost to the public purse of the UK's military presence in the Baltic region in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","28577"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455279","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-03","<p>As noted in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, Russia is mid-way through a programme of major investment to modernise and upgrade its military, including its nuclear forces. Its behaviour will continue to be hard to predict, and, though highly unlikely, we cannot rule out the possibility that it may feel tempted to act aggressively against NATO Allies.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-03-03T16:01:11.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455279/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455279/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455279/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Russia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the military threat to the UK posed by Russia.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","28578"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455280","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-01","<p>Every element of the Successor Programme has now commenced Stage 2 design.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-03-01T17:01:26.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455280/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455280/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455280/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Trident Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of the elements of the Successor programme have commenced Stage 2; and when he expects all elements of that programme to have commenced Stage 2.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","28582"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455281","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-01","<p>The Successor submarine programme remains in the Assessment Phase. I am withholding internal Ministry Of Defence forecasts on future programme expenditure as disclosure would or would be likely to prejudice the Department's commercial interests.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-03-01T17:00:42.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455281/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455281/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455281/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-25","Trident Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the forecast expenditure is on the Successor programme within his Department's 10 year equipment plan.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","28583"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455282","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-04","<p>The payment of overtime is permitted where a Ministry of Defence (MOD) employee below the Senior Civil Service is required to work beyond conditioned hours or on days that they would not normally be required to work. There has been a conscious effort to reduce overtime costs in the MOD, line managers must scrutinise overtime and encourage time off in lieu as an alternative. As a guiding principle, overtime should only be granted when taken in direct support of current operations, it is of essential business resilience, or when posts require routinely long hours and time off in lieu no longer represents a realistic alternative.</p><p> </p><p>A summary of the amount of MOD expenditure on overtime payments in the last 24 months is shown below.</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Month</p></td><td><p>£ million</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>March 2014</p></td><td><p>3.550</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2014</p></td><td><p>5.990</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>May 2014</p></td><td><p>4.908</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>June 2014</p></td><td><p>7.172</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>July 2014</p></td><td><p>5.560</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>August 2014</p></td><td><p>5.744</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>September 2014</p></td><td><p>5.305</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>October 2014</p></td><td><p>7.050</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>November 2014</p></td><td><p>6.378</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>December 2014</p></td><td><p>5.416</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January 2015</p></td><td><p>4.820</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>February 2015</p></td><td><p>6.726</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>March 2015</p></td><td><p>3.895</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2015</p></td><td><p>5.018</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>May 2015</p></td><td><p>6.605</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>June 2015</p></td><td><p>6.039</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>July 2015</p></td><td><p>6.481</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>August 2015</p></td><td><p>6.313</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>September 2015</p></td><td><p>4.603</p>