"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455304","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-03-01","<p>The capacity of existing Capacity Market Units awarded Capacity Market agreements including those awarded refurbishing agreements was:</p><p> </p><p>a) 46,464MW in 2014; and</p><p>b) 42,099 MW in 2015.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-03-01T13:08:38.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455304/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455304/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455304/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-25","Electricity Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what capacity of existing Capacity Market Units were awarded Capacity Market contracts in (a) 2014 and (b) 2015.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","28533"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455305","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-03-01","<p>All existing Capacity Market Units (CMU) participating in the 2014 and 2015 auctions submitted exit bids in accordance with the auction rules. Confidentiality rules mean that the Government is unable to obtain from National Grid, the delivery body for the Capacity Market, the detailed information on individual exit bids.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-03-01T15:32:44.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455305/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455305/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455305/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-25","Electricity Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what proportion of existing capacity of existing Capacity Market Units that were awarded Capacity Market contracts did not place an exit bid in (a) 2014 and (b) 2015.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","28534"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455306","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-03-04","<p>When the Human Rights Act came into force, no specific arrangements were put in place by the then government to record cases in the way requested.</p><p> </p><p>Litigants in civil cases can rely on arguments based wholly or partly on the Human Rights Act 1998. In some cases, the Act is relied on in addition to other claims. Neither Government Legal Department (GLD) records nor the County and High Courts case management systems distinguish between cases where the Act is invoked and cases where it is not. As a result, there are not currently data published which distinguish between cases where the Human Rights Act was or was not invoked.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-03-04T13:30:52.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455306/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455306/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455306/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-25","Department for Energy and Climate Change: Human Rights Act 1998","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many civil law suits have been brought against her Department based either wholly or partially on grounds provided by the Human Rights Act 1998; how many such suits were settled out of court before a court judgment was delivered; and how much such settlements have cost the public purse since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28639"
