/455308/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-02-25","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Overtime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much her Department has paid to staff in overtime in each of the last 24 months.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28688"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455309","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-03-04","<p>The Human Rights Act 1998 has been in force since October 2000. There is no central record of civil cases brought against Defra where a breach of the Human Rights Act 1998 was alleged.</p><p>There have not been any cases since 2010 settled by payment of damages which alleged a breach of the Human Rights Act 1998.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-03-04T10:33:58.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455309/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455309/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455309/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-02-25","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Human Rights Act 1998","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many civil law suits have been brought against her Department based either wholly or partially on grounds provided by the Human Rights Act 1998; how many such suits were settled out of court before a court judgment was delivered; and how much such settlements have cost the public purse since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28640"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455310","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-03-01","<p>The Environment Agency is continuing to investigate the case of illegal dumping on land in Cornwall Road. As this is an active investigation I am unable to provide further details at this stage.</p><p> </p><p>Illegal dumping and waste crime more generally is unacceptable whether it occurs on public or private land.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is taking action to crack down on this unacceptable behaviour and has pledged an additional £20 million of funding for waste crime enforcement over the next five years as part of the Spending Review. We are also working with the Environment Agency through a joint Waste Crime Action Plan to ensure its regulatory effort is targeted effectively and focussed on speedy and tough enforcement action</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-03-01T10:19:24.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455310/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455310/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455310/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-02-25","Fly-tipping: Smeltwich","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps the Environment Agency has taken to identify those responsible for the fly-tipping of plastic and other rubbish in Cornwall Road, Smethwick in March 2015.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","28522"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455311","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-03-01","<p>The Environment Agency can already refuse an application for an environmental permit if it considers the applicant or another relevant person is not competent or unwilling to comply with the conditions of a permit. Where disclosed as part of an application, relevant convictions may be considered by the regulator as part of its assessment of an operator’s competence to hold an environmental permit.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-03-01T10:05:19.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455311/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455311/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455311/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-02-25","Waste Disposal: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will make it her policy that waste disposal licences are not issued by the Environment Agency to individuals with criminal convictions or to companies controlled by individuals with criminal convictions.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","28520"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455312","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-03-04","<p>The Govt Legal Dept have represented Defra at Employment Tribunals since Oct 2011. The costs of any such litigation are covered by an annual block fee arrangement which covers all aspects of legal services provided to Defra.</p><p>The cost of Employment Tribunals can be found within the HMCTS annual accounts published at<em>: </em><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/433948/hmcts-annual-report-accounts-2014-15.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/433948/hmcts-annual-report-accounts-2014-15.pdf</a>.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-03-04T13:33:00.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455312/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455312/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455312/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-02-25","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Employment Tribunals Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much her Department spent from the public purse on industrial tribunals in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28624"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455313","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-03-04","<p>Cleaning services for Defra are provided under the facilities contract with Interserve FM. Rates for cleaners vary dependent on location and market rates. From April the minimum rates will be:</p><p>£7.20 per hour for 25 year olds and over</p><p>£6.70 per hour for 21 year olds and over</p><p>£5.30 per hour for 18 – 20 year olds</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-03-04T13:46:08.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455313/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455313/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455313/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-02-25","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Cleaning Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what the rate of pay is for cleaners in her Department.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","28604"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455314","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-03-04","<p>This Department’s publications and consultations issued since August 2012 are available, indexed in date order, on the GOV.UK website. The indexes enable users to search by date and by type of publication. Approximately 2540 publications have been issued by, or jointly with, this Department since August 2012, including 210 consultations. We cannot identify any circulars published since August 2012.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-03-04T11:04:19.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455314/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455314/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455314/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-02-25","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Publications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many (a) publications, (b) consultation documents and (c) circulars her Department has issued since August 2012; and what the title was of each such publication, consultation document or circular.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455315","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-03-02","<p>No consultants’ contracts were terminated early in each of the last six years.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-03-02T12:04:21.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455315/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455315/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455315/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-02-25","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many consultants' contracts were terminated early in each of the last six years for which figures are available; and what the cost of each such termination was in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455316","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-01","<p>Decisions regarding the disbursement of any funding will be made once we have received confirmation of whether our application has been successful.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-03-01T17:05:31.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455316/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455316/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455316/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-25","European Union Solidarity Fund: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether the Government plans to make available to the Welsh Government funds received as a result of the application to the EU Solidarity Fund announced on 25 February 2016.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","28446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455317","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-01","<p>The UK Government has been working with Wales and Scotland to understand their impacts from the flooding events of 2015 and early 2016. These conversations will continue to enable us to demonstrate the impacts to the UK for an EU Solidarity Fund application.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-03-01T17:04:52.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455317/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455317/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455317/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-25","European Union Solidarity Fund: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what representations he has received from the Welsh Government on applying to the EU Solidarity Fund as a result of flooding in Wales in late 2015 and early 2016.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","28447"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455318","Department for International Development","false","2016-03-01","<p>The British Embassy regularly engages with the National Unity Government on improving extractives governance to encourage responsible development of the extractives sector. The UK-funded Extractive Sector Support Programme provides technical advice to the Ministry of Mines and Petroleum on legal and regulatory frameworks, contract management and fiscal regimes. The UK is also helping the Afghan Government to implement the Extractives Industry Transparency Initiative. I raised this matter when I met President Ghani in June 2015.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2016-03-01T17:08:50.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455318/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455318/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455318/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-02-25","Afghanistan: Mining","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what political engagement her Department had with the Afghan government on extractives governance in 2015.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","28433"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455319","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-03","<p>This information is not held centrally and the question cannot be answered without incurring disproportionate cost.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-03-03T16:47:45.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455319/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455319/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455319/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-25","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many consultants' contracts were terminated early in each of the last six years for which figures are available; and what the cost of each such termination was in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28657"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455320","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-07","<p>Over 3,500 Foreign and Commonwealth Office publications since 1 August 2012 are available on the gov.uk website at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications</a></p><p>Many of our Posts and Missions overseas publish documents that are relevant to their work. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office does not hold information on the full range of documents centrally and it could be obtained only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-03-07T15:52:03.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455320/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455320/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455320/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-25","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Publications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many (a) publications, (b) consultation documents and (c) circulars his Department has issued since August 2012; and what the title was of each such publication, consultation document or circular.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455321","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-04","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) contracts out cleaning services relating to the FCO's UK estate to Interserve as part of its facilities management contract. Interserve are responsible for setting rates of pay for their staff. They have informed the FCO that they currently pay £7.04 per hour to staff for cleaning the FCO’s buildings.</p><p>The National Living Wage will come into effect on 1 April and all employers, including Interserve, will be required to pay all staff, aged 25 years and above a minimum of £7.20 per hour.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-03-04T14:27:46.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455321/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455321/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455321/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-25","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Cleaning Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the rate of pay is for cleaners in his Department.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","28605"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455322","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-07","The Decision of the Heads of State or Government, meeting within the European Council, on 18 and 19 February 2016 is not subject to the provisions of the Constitutional Reform and Governance Act 2010.","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-03-07T15:49:20.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455322/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455322/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455322/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-25","UK membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the compliance of the Decision of the Heads of State or Government, meeting within the European Council, on 18 and 19 February 2016 with Part 2 of the Constitutional Reform and Governance Act 2010; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris","28549"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455323","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-03","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office's (FCO) legal fees for employment tribunals for the last twelve months, where invoices have so far been received (January 2015 - December 2015), total £46,385.52. The FCO is in the process of recovering £3,000 of this following a Costs Order in our favour.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-03-03T11:37:51.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455323/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455323/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455323/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-25","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Employment Tribunals Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how much his Department spent from the public purse on industrial tribunals in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28625"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455324","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-03","<p>We are clear that Israel has legal obligations as an Occupying Power with respect to the Occupied Palestinian Territories under the Fourth of the Geneva Conventions of 1949. This includes Article 49, which prohibits deportation of protected persons from the occupied territory and Article 76, providing that protected persons convicted of offenses shall be detained and serve their sentences within the occupied territory. We regularly talk to the Government of Israel with regard to the implementation of those obligations and raise our serious concerns, including about the treatment of Palestinian children that are arrested and detained in Israeli prisons. We have been clear with Israel that forcible transfer would be a breach of international humanitarian law and would have serious ramifications on Israel’s international standing.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-03-03T11:34:05.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455324/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455324/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455324/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-25","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the compatibility with international law of the arrest and transfer of children from the Occupied Palestinian Territories to Israel.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Mr Gavin Shuker","28493"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455325","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-01","<p>The Decision of the Heads of State or Government, meeting within the European Council, on 18 and 19 February 2016 is a treaty as defined in section 25(1) of the Constitutional Reform and Governance Act 2010. Given that no ratification procedures apply to the Decision, the obligations in section 20 of the Act do not apply.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-03-01T17:43:31.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455325/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455325/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455325/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-25","UK membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the Decision of the Heads of State or Government, meeting within the European Council, on 18 and 19 February 2016, is an international Treaty to which the procedures of sections 20 and 25 of the Constitutional Reform and Governance Act 2010 will apply.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","28490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455326","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-03","<p>At the February European Council the Government negotiated a new settlement, giving the United Kingdom a special status in a reformed European Union. The Government's position, as set out by the Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), to the House on 22 February, is that the UK will be stronger, safer and better off remaining in a reformed EU.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-03-03T16:44:48.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455326/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455326/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455326/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-25","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to the Prime Minister's Oral Statement of 22 February 2016, Official Report, column 35, on the European Council, whether his Department is undertaking planning in the eventuality of a majority leave vote in the EU referendum.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","28502"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455327","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-03","We do not have any record of refugees from the Democratic People’s Republic of Korea approaching Our Embassy in Beijing or our Consulates in China to claim safe passage or asylum in the last 10 years.","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2016-03-03T11:54:39.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455327/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455327/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455327/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-25","North Korea: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many North Korean refugees have approached the British Embassy or Consulate in China for safe passage or asylum in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","28546"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455328","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-03","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office does not hold detailed information on the number of defections from the Democratic People’s Republic of Korea (DPRK). Information on defections from the DPRK can be obtained from the Republic of Korea’s Ministry of Unification</p><p>http://eng.unikorea.go.kr/content.do?cmsid=3026</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2016-03-03T15:44:05.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455328/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455328/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455328/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-25","North Korea: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what information his Department holds on the number of (a) defections from North Korea and (b) unsuccessful defection attempts from that country in the last four years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","28545"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455329","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-03","<p>We regularly raise the treatment of North Korean refugees in multilateral fora such as the United Nations Security Council and the Human Rights Council. We raise our concerns around refoulement regularly at the annual UK-China Human Rights Dialogue and through our Embassy in Beijing. In addition, we work directly with the Chinese authorities on a number of projects to counter human trafficking, which seek to protect the most vulnerable from exploitation, abuse, neglect and violence. We made bilateral representations to Laos in 2013 (see written answer HL950) regarding the refoulement of DPRK refuges. We have not made any specific representations to Vietnam or Burma on DPRK refugees, but we continue to maintain a dialogue on human rights issues with these countries.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2016-03-03T15:41:16.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455329/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455329/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455329/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-25","North Korea: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations his Department has made to (a) China, (b) Laos, (c) Vietnam and (d) Myanmar on the repatriation of North Korean defectors from those countries to North Korea.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","28544"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455330","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-04","<p>The information requested is not available, as separate data for cases based wholly or partially on the Human Rights Act 1998 are not recorded.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-03-04T14:58:57.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455330/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455330/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455330/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-25","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Human Rights Act 1998","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many civil law suits have been brought against his Department based either wholly or partially on grounds provided by the Human Rights Act 1998; how many such suits were settled out of court before a court judgment was delivered; and how much such settlements have cost the public purse since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455331","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-07","<p>The Decision of the Heads of State or Government, meeting within the European Council, on 18 and 19 February 2016, meets the definition of a treaty under Article 2 of the Vienna Convention on the Law of Treaties. The Decision was registered at the United Nations Treaty Office on 24 February 2016.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-03-07T15:50:56.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455331/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455331/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455331/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-25","UK membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the Decision of the Heads of State or Government, meeting within the European Council, on 18 and 19 February 2016, meets the definition of a treaty under Article 2 of the Vienna Convention on the Law of Treaties.","false","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris","28571"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455332","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-09","<p>It is for the relevant national authorities in other Member States to determine their constitutional requirements and potential legal proceedings.</p><p>The Decision of the Heads of State or Government, meeting within the European Council, on 18 and 19 February 2016 was agreed to by all Member States and is now a legally binding document that has been registered with the United Nations as an international treaty.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-03-09T15:58:46.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455332/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455332/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455332/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-25","UK membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what notification he has received on whether there are (a) constitutional requirements and (b) potential legal proceedings in other EU member states related to the Decision of the Heads of State or Government, meeting within the European Council, on 18 and 19 February 2016.","false","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris","28569"
